(She decides to go big and aims for the whole branch.)

269
00:12:24,103 --> 00:12:26,373
I must go somewhere else. This won't do.

270
00:12:26,873 --> 00:12:29,003
I must move.

271
00:12:30,173 --> 00:12:38,013
(Finding a new land of coconuts)

272
00:12:38,513 --> 00:12:40,113
(Panting)

273
00:12:40,453 --> 00:12:42,983
(Struggling)

274
00:12:44,323 --> 00:12:48,123
(Toddling)

275
00:12:48,653 --> 00:12:50,393
(Laughing)

276
00:12:51,393 --> 00:12:53,133
The pole is way bigger than her.

277
00:12:53,263 --> 00:12:54,263
What?

278
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:57,833
(She finds it funny as well.)

279
00:12:58,003 --> 00:13:01,603
It's hard for me to even handle this pole!

280
00:13:02,543 --> 00:13:04,579
- That's how it is for me. - That's how it looks, Hye Yoon.

281
00:13:04,603 --> 00:13:06,613
- Where are they? There they are! - Be careful!

282
00:13:08,143 --> 00:13:09,512
Let's find the coconuts.

283
00:13:09,513 --> 00:13:10,793
(I'll pick all of the coconuts.)

284
00:13:11,313 --> 00:13:13,352
(She spots the right coconut tree.)

285
00:13:13,353 --> 00:13:15,153
Let's do this, Hye Yoon.

286
00:13:16,483 --> 00:13:18,182
I'm sure there's a way to do this.

287
00:13:18,183 --> 00:13:20,463
(She finally finds a tree that looks easy to go against.)

288
00:13:20,993 --> 00:13:22,793
Hold on. I need a break.

289
00:13:23,223 --> 00:13:24,223
(She takes a short break as she moved a long way.)

290
00:13:24,224 --> 00:13:25,593
I moved from all the way there.

291
00:13:27,233 --> 00:13:28,903
Can't I just climb up?

292
00:13:29,403 --> 00:13:30,603
It's right there.

293
00:13:31,263 --> 00:13:32,402
It isn't that high up.

294
00:13:32,403 --> 00:13:33,643
(It looks like an easy height.)

295
00:13:35,133 --> 00:13:37,643
(Will she climb up like Dex?)

296
00:13:38,503 --> 00:13:40,183
There was a reason why the knife was used.

297
00:13:41,473 --> 00:13:43,282
It's slippery as a slide.

298
00:13:43,283 --> 00:13:45,123
(The surface of the coconut tree is slippery.)

299
00:13:45,883 --> 00:13:51,383
(She tries to make the steps just as she was taught.)

300
00:13:53,423 --> 00:13:55,763
Hye Yoon! Are you going to climb up?

301
00:13:55,893 --> 00:13:57,493
This one isn't that tall!

302
00:13:58,123 --> 00:14:00,463
It was really slippery, though. I just want to get these.

303
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,133
She's so cute.

304
00:14:04,903 --> 00:14:06,003
I'll give it a try.

305
00:14:06,703 --> 00:14:09,043
I think it's worth a try as the tree isn't that tall.

306
00:14:10,603 --> 00:14:12,713
It's for us to collect 80 coconuts.

307
00:14:14,313 --> 00:14:15,412
For 80 coconuts!

308
00:14:15,413 --> 00:14:17,113
(Burning with ambition)

309
00:14:17,683 --> 00:14:24,783
(Work music can be heard all of a sudden.)

310
00:14:25,253 --> 00:14:29,162
(It's as if the sad melody describes the hearts of the siblings.)

311
00:14:29,163 --> 00:14:30,923
Gosh, why does the song sound so sad?

312
00:14:33,293 --> 00:14:38,873
(Jung Ah takes the time to listen.)

313
00:14:39,173 --> 00:14:42,033
(Hye Yoon gets ready to climb up after taking off her shoes.)

314
00:14:44,673 --> 00:14:46,212
(Laughing)

315
00:14:46,213 --> 00:14:47,613
(Chuckling)

316
00:14:47,873 --> 00:14:49,683
(Sliding down)

317
00:14:52,313 --> 00:14:53,852
(Hye Yoon tries her best with her socks on, )

318
00:14:53,853 --> 00:14:55,283
(but she fails.)

319
00:14:56,153 --> 00:14:59,153
- Gosh! - Gosh, I want to cry.

320
00:15:00,753 --> 00:15:03,593
The song sounds so sad. You doing that makes it even sadder.

321
00:15:05,063 --> 00:15:08,363
Why is this so high up?

322
00:15:11,163 --> 00:15:12,933
It's such a sweet melody.

323
00:15:15,073 --> 00:15:16,443
I want to get a coconut as well!

324
00:15:19,443 --> 00:15:22,213
I should move over to the flat land. I can't do this.

325
00:15:23,483 --> 00:15:24,483
(Getting up)

326
00:15:24,484 --> 00:15:26,883
Gosh, I feel so annoyed. I should give it a smack.

327
00:15:28,683 --> 00:15:30,022
(Leader Yum has come to give the coconuts a smack.)

328
00:15:30,023 --> 00:15:31,123
Move away.

329
00:15:32,523 --> 00:15:33,652
(Did you give Hye Yoon a hard time?)

330
00:15:33,653 --> 00:15:34,923
I think this will work.

331
00:15:36,093 --> 00:15:38,623
(Leader Yum is here.)

332
00:15:39,093 --> 00:15:40,833
- Get ready. - Press it down.

333
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:42,232
(The coconut branch gets bent helplessly.)

334
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:44,033
- Gosh! It's working! - It's working!

335
00:15:44,963 --> 00:15:46,003
Turn it!

336
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:48,003
I'm too short!

337
00:15:48,873 --> 00:15:50,742
(Struggling)

338
00:15:50,743 --> 00:15:52,812
Hold on. I think you should hold onto this.

339
00:15:52,813 --> 00:15:53,813
I'm too short.

340
00:15:53,814 --> 00:15:55,412
Make sure to keep it down.

341
00:15:55,413 --> 00:15:56,413
Right.

342
00:15:57,013 --> 00:15:59,813
(Hye Yoon takes the pole.)

343
00:16:00,553 --> 00:16:05,583
(I'm going to pull out your hair, coconut!)

344
00:16:06,823 --> 00:16:07,823
Gosh, I can't do it.

345
00:16:07,824 --> 00:16:10,223
- Wasn't there a sickle? - The knife?

346
00:16:10,323 --> 00:16:12,592
The knife. Hold onto it.

347
00:16:12,593 --> 00:16:14,333
(They switch to the second method.)

348
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,232
I won't let you go.

349
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:17,662
(I won't let you go, coconut.)

350
00:16:17,663 --> 00:16:21,303
You've met your match today.

351
00:16:24,673 --> 00:16:26,773
(She hits it in advance with the knife.)

352
00:16:26,873 --> 00:16:28,643
(She places down the knife.)

353
00:16:29,543 --> 00:16:31,913
(Is she finishing it off with her hands?)

354
00:16:32,353 --> 00:16:34,252
(The coconut gets knocked out.)

355
00:16:34,253 --> 00:16:35,453
We did it!

356
00:16:36,283 --> 00:16:38,653
(She finally manages to pick one with Jung Ah's help.)

357
00:16:39,393 --> 00:16:42,823
(It's hard to pick a single coconut.)

358
00:16:44,993 --> 00:16:46,932
I think we're way off from picking 80 coconuts at this rate.

359
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:48,539
(I think we're way off from picking 80 coconuts at this rate.)

360
00:16:48,563 --> 00:16:50,802
(After 30 minutes of coconut picking)

361
00:16:50,803 --> 00:16:54,203
(Dex: 4, Jung Ah: 3, Hye Yoon: 1, Jun Myun: 0)

362
00:16:54,573 --> 00:16:56,942
Gosh, I feel exhausted.

363
00:16:56,943 --> 00:17:04,943
(They must pick 72 more to reach their goal of 80.)

364
00:17:05,043 --> 00:17:06,183
- Gosh. - Where...

365
00:17:07,283 --> 00:17:11,223
(Will they fail to earn the coin?)

366
00:17:12,053 --> 00:17:13,322
(Dex switches to using the ladder.)

367
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:14,393
Gosh!

368
00:17:16,023 --> 00:17:17,963
(Acting silly)

369
00:17:19,793 --> 00:17:20,793
(Obtaining 1 coconut)
(There's no giving up.)

370
00:17:22,603 --> 00:17:23,603
(Obtaining 1 coconut)

371
00:17:25,103 --> 00:17:27,873
(Dex speeds up after switching to the ladder.)

372
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:29,343
(Obtaining 1 coconut)

373
00:17:31,973 --> 00:17:36,943
(He's collecting the coconuts at an immense speed.)

374
00:17:38,283 --> 00:17:39,583
The ladder is easy to use.

375
00:17:41,213 --> 00:17:43,483
I already collected this much. There are 2, 4, 6...

376
00:17:43,983 --> 00:17:45,183
Eight, nine.

377
00:17:46,253 --> 00:17:47,723
That's ten of them.

378
00:17:48,493 --> 00:17:49,813
We'll be able to collect 80 soon.

379
00:17:52,793 --> 00:17:55,363
That's seven. You're dead meat.

380
00:17:58,933 --> 00:17:59,933
There we go.

381
00:17:59,934 --> 00:18:01,449
(Jung Ah gets the hang of it and collects 8.)

382
00:18:01,473 --> 00:18:04,843
(Picking up the coconuts is a lot of work as well.)

383
00:18:05,143 --> 00:18:06,373
Gosh, my neck.

384
00:18:09,043 --> 00:18:10,942
(Hye Yoon switched to the ladder in the meanwhile.)

385
00:18:10,943 --> 00:18:13,383
It feels a bit off. Hold on.

386
00:18:13,853 --> 00:18:15,113
(Swaying)

387
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:19,093
(She's struggling even with the ladder.)

388
00:18:19,193 --> 00:18:20,223
I'm okay.

389
00:18:20,693 --> 00:18:21,693
Right.

390
00:18:22,863 --> 00:18:24,263
Should I go between it and lift it?

391
00:18:24,893 --> 00:18:25,893
(Stable)

392
00:18:26,493 --> 00:18:27,692
Gosh.

393
00:18:27,693 --> 00:18:28,962
(She becomes a human train all of a sudden.)

394
00:18:28,963 --> 00:18:31,763
I don't know what I'm doing, but what do you think?

395
00:18:34,873 --> 00:18:38,443
It looks too dangerous for the chick.

396
00:18:38,503 --> 00:18:39,513
Hey, baby!

397
00:18:41,373 --> 00:18:44,043
Why did you run away from home? Go back home!

398
00:18:44,443 --> 00:18:47,883
You should head back in as well! Hurry!

399
00:18:49,223 --> 00:18:50,922
You can't come this way.

400
00:18:50,923 --> 00:18:52,222
The world is a dangerous place.

401
00:18:52,223 --> 00:18:53,753
You might get hit by the coconuts.

402
00:18:55,023 --> 00:18:56,823
I'm telling you to head back in. Gosh.

403
00:18:58,293 --> 00:19:00,633
(She climbs up the ladder after nagging at the chick.)

404
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:03,833
(She seems to have no fear as she climbs up.)

405
00:19:06,073 --> 00:19:07,073
Right.

406
00:19:07,533 --> 00:19:09,943
(The brave youngest, Hye Yoon)

407
00:19:10,473 --> 00:19:12,443
(Touching)

408
00:19:14,643 --> 00:19:15,843
(Twisting)

409
00:19:16,543 --> 00:19:19,013
(It won't budge.)

410
00:19:19,753 --> 00:19:21,883
Why is it so tough?

411
00:19:23,423 --> 00:19:25,703
(It's hard to pick them as they are close to each other.)

412
00:19:26,053 --> 00:19:27,293
I need a break.

413
00:19:30,093 --> 00:19:31,993
Gosh.

414
00:19:32,093 --> 00:19:33,662
It's so tough.

415
00:19:33,663 --> 00:19:34,762
It looks like you're rubbing against it.

416
00:19:34,763 --> 00:19:37,103
Right. I'm rubbing against it...

417
00:19:37,763 --> 00:19:38,763
to see if it grew well.

418
00:19:42,273 --> 00:19:45,342
(Smart Hye Yoon figures out how to do it right away.)

419
00:19:45,343 --> 00:19:46,343
(Obtaining 1 coconut)

420
00:19:47,643 --> 00:19:48,643
(Obtaining 1 coconut)

421
00:19:49,043 --> 00:19:50,113
I'll throw it down!

422
00:19:50,983 --> 00:19:51,983
That's two.

423
00:19:54,513 --> 00:19:55,513
(Obtaining 1 coconut)

424
00:19:55,713 --> 00:19:56,753
That's three!

425
00:19:57,453 --> 00:20:01,193
(She finally gets adjusted after using different methods.)

426
00:20:01,693 --> 00:20:03,292
A tree of this height is perfect.

427
00:20:03,293 --> 00:20:05,399
(While Hye Yoon is excitedly collecting the coconuts, )

428
00:20:05,423 --> 00:20:07,733
(Dex is also working hard on the ladder to pick them.)

429
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:11,063
(He even gets on top of the tree.)

430
00:20:13,873 --> 00:20:15,032
There we go.

431
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:17,403
(The coconuts roll down as soon as he picks them.)

432
00:20:17,573 --> 00:20:19,542
Where are the two I just picked?

433
00:20:19,543 --> 00:20:20,712
- They rolled down. - They rolled down.

434
00:20:20,713 --> 00:20:21,793
They went all the way down?

435
00:20:22,173 --> 00:20:25,283
No! My coconuts!

436
00:20:28,653 --> 00:20:29,682
Gosh!

437
00:20:29,683 --> 00:20:30,859
(Is this like pouring coconut water into a sieve?)

438
00:20:30,883 --> 00:20:32,323
Stop it from rolling down!

439
00:20:35,963 --> 00:20:37,063
Be careful!

440
00:20:37,263 --> 00:20:41,893
(The coconuts roll down the hill.)

441
00:20:43,303 --> 00:20:44,903
I'll use the knife again.

442
00:20:45,063 --> 00:20:47,232
Don't collect the ones on the slope.

443
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,303
We won't be able to count them as they roll down.

444
00:20:49,503 --> 00:20:50,503
Right.

445
00:20:51,143 --> 00:20:53,812
(Jun Myun picks up the coconuts that have rolled down.)

446
00:20:53,813 --> 00:20:57,413
It's too heavy for me. I'll just pick up the coconuts.

447
00:20:57,843 --> 00:20:58,983
I have no strength.

448
00:21:00,483 --> 00:21:01,513
I'm serious.

449
00:21:03,623 --> 00:21:07,853
(Sullen)

450
00:21:09,963 --> 00:21:11,823
I'll eat less for dinner.

451
00:21:16,203 --> 00:21:21,172
(She works hard to pick up the coconuts as she feels bad.)

452
00:21:21,173 --> 00:21:22,403
They're all down there.

453
00:21:23,043 --> 00:21:25,042
The pole is too heavy for me.

454
00:21:25,043 --> 00:21:27,483
- I couldn't pick a single one. - You won't be able to do it.

455
00:21:29,943 --> 00:21:34,113
(I'll collect the coconuts instead.)

456
00:21:38,553 --> 00:21:42,593
This is way too difficult.

457
00:21:43,293 --> 00:21:45,123
The pole is too heavy.

458
00:21:50,363 --> 00:21:51,732
- It's rolling down! - No!

459
00:21:51,733 --> 00:21:53,133
- What a loss! - Gosh!

460
00:21:56,473 --> 00:21:57,542
(The coconuts roll down after a hassle to pick them.)

461
00:21:57,543 --> 00:21:58,743
Another one rolled down?

462
00:22:00,243 --> 00:22:02,372
Gosh, I can't do this. I feel so exhausted.

463
00:22:02,373 --> 00:22:05,183
(She falls to the ground as she's too exhausted.)

464
00:22:05,513 --> 00:22:06,752
Where did it roll down to?

465
00:22:06,753 --> 00:22:09,723
(A total of 25 coconuts were collected after 50 minutes.)

466
00:22:09,923 --> 00:22:11,823
(Meanwhile...)

467
00:22:12,183 --> 00:22:15,093
(A guest has come to surprise the siblings.)

468
00:22:15,353 --> 00:22:17,393
(Lee Si Eon)

469
00:22:17,763 --> 00:22:19,563
It seems obvious, doesn't it?

470
00:22:21,093 --> 00:22:23,833
(He gets disguised perfectly as a cameraman.)

471
00:22:23,933 --> 00:22:25,402
I'll do this.

472
00:22:25,403 --> 00:22:27,432
(He's getting himself ready with a rehearsal.)

473
00:22:27,433 --> 00:22:28,433
Right?

474
00:22:28,903 --> 00:22:30,342
He catches on really quickly...

475
00:22:30,343 --> 00:22:31,742
and is full of suspicion.

476
00:22:31,743 --> 00:22:33,623
(Goal: Fool Dex, the one that is quick-witted.)

477
00:22:34,113 --> 00:22:35,442
Gosh, I feel nervous.

478
00:22:35,443 --> 00:22:37,483
(Will he be able to appear without getting caught?)

479
00:22:37,843 --> 00:22:39,913
Are we almost there? They're down there.

480
00:22:41,513 --> 00:22:43,322
Let's get closer.

481
00:22:43,323 --> 00:22:44,323
(Whispering)

482
00:22:45,453 --> 00:22:48,953
(He gets closer while checking his surroundings.)

483
00:22:51,423 --> 00:22:54,493
(He happened to appear right in front of Leader Yum.)

484
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,309
(Will he get caught by Leader Yum even before making an appearance?)

485
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:59,503
(Flustered)

486
00:22:59,973 --> 00:23:02,332
(Jung Ah didn't seem to notice.)

487
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:04,273
(Feeling relieved)

488
00:23:04,873 --> 00:23:07,313
(They don't recognize him even if he walks right past them.)

489
00:23:09,313 --> 00:23:10,583
Call me Director Park.

490
00:23:10,683 --> 00:23:11,683
Director Park.

491
00:23:12,183 --> 00:23:13,812
Should we move that way, Director Park?

492
00:23:13,813 --> 00:23:14,853
Right.

493
00:23:15,653 --> 00:23:17,723
(Director Park climbs the tree to film Dex?)

494
00:23:18,053 --> 00:23:19,722
- Good? - Yes. I'm holding onto it.

495
00:23:19,723 --> 00:23:20,963
(Dex is right in front of him.)

496
00:23:21,453 --> 00:23:25,363
(Does the target not know who is ten steps away from him?)

497
00:23:26,333 --> 00:23:30,763
(Director Park manages to hide himself.)

498
00:23:32,873 --> 00:23:36,473
(Without knowing what is going on, )

499
00:23:37,673 --> 00:23:41,413
(young lamb Dex is focused just on collecting the coconuts.)

500
00:23:42,613 --> 00:23:44,912
(He charges forward to Director Park's tree...)

501
00:23:44,913 --> 00:23:47,183
(without knowing anything.)

502
00:23:47,283 --> 00:23:48,312
(Lee Si Eon's camera)

503
00:23:48,313 --> 00:23:49,882
- Come down slowly. - Right.

504
00:23:49,883 --> 00:23:51,723
(He does the V sign without knowing anything.)

505
00:23:51,823 --> 00:23:54,823
(Laughing)

506
00:23:55,923 --> 00:24:00,293
(His closest friend is right in front of him, )

507
00:24:00,793 --> 00:24:04,533
(but Dex is only focused on the coconuts.)

508
00:24:05,233 --> 00:24:09,503
(He doesn't notice anything wrong when he's right there.)

509
00:24:09,843 --> 00:24:12,503
(With his friend who seems to be clueless, )

510
00:24:13,243 --> 00:24:15,943
(he makes a bolder move to get closer.)

511
00:24:16,313 --> 00:24:20,483
(Pretending to film an insert shot)

512
00:24:21,453 --> 00:24:22,952
(Laughing)

513
00:24:22,953 --> 00:24:24,253
(Biting the coconut)

514
00:24:25,553 --> 00:24:28,153
(Dex climbs up another tree to collect the coconuts.)

515
00:24:28,893 --> 00:24:30,063
I'll get hit by the coconut.

516
00:24:30,363 --> 00:24:32,363
I'll get hit by it.

517
00:24:33,463 --> 00:24:35,663
(Dex cuts the coconut branch without knowing anything.)

518
00:24:35,693 --> 00:24:37,703
(Here comes the coconut.)

519
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:41,033
(He dribbles the coconut naturally.)

520
00:24:41,973 --> 00:24:43,243
(Doing his best to act)

521
00:24:47,213 --> 00:24:49,012
- Are you okay? - Hold on.

522
00:24:49,013 --> 00:24:51,343
(His acting begins in earnest.)

523
00:24:54,353 --> 00:24:55,512
(Limping)

524
00:24:55,513 --> 00:24:56,683
Are you okay, sir?

525
00:24:57,283 --> 00:24:58,723
What happened?

526
00:24:59,493 --> 00:25:01,553
What? He got hit by the coconut?

527
00:25:02,963 --> 00:25:05,463
(Freezing)

528
00:25:05,793 --> 00:25:07,062
The coconut that was rolling down?

529
00:25:07,063 --> 00:25:08,539
(Dex gets flustered after hearing that he got hit by his coconut.)

530
00:25:08,563 --> 00:25:11,333
(Worried)

531
00:25:12,563 --> 00:25:13,633
Are you okay?

532
00:25:14,173 --> 00:25:15,773
- Yes. - Gosh, I'm sorry.

533
00:25:15,933 --> 00:25:17,372
Oh, no. Where did it hit you?

534
00:25:17,373 --> 00:25:18,373
Over here.

535
00:25:20,113 --> 00:25:21,543
- Here? - Yes.

536
00:25:21,843 --> 00:25:22,882
- Here? - Yes.

537
00:25:22,883 --> 00:25:25,583
(Dex checks to see if he's seriously injured.)

538
00:25:26,383 --> 00:25:28,113
- Right here. - On this side?

539
00:25:29,153 --> 00:25:32,223
(Did he make eye contact with Dex?)

540
00:25:33,053 --> 00:25:34,923
Lower your leg for a minute.

541
00:25:36,763 --> 00:25:39,223
(Worried that the injury is serious)

542
00:25:39,963 --> 00:25:41,863
Do we have a cold water bottle or ice?

543
00:25:42,733 --> 00:25:44,232
(Checking the condition of his foot again)

544
00:25:44,233 --> 00:25:45,332
- I'm sorry... - Goodness.

545
00:25:45,333 --> 00:25:47,233
(Screaming)

546
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:49,673
(Gosh...)

547
00:25:50,003 --> 00:25:51,072
Wait.

548
00:25:51,073 --> 00:25:52,372
(Pouring with acting skills)

549
00:25:52,373 --> 00:25:53,773
This seems serious.

550
00:25:54,673 --> 00:25:55,742
- Hold on. - Gosh.

551
00:25:55,743 --> 00:25:58,483
(He's completely convinced by the incredible acting.)

552
00:25:59,583 --> 00:26:00,812
Did he fall down?

553
00:26:00,813 --> 00:26:03,373
(Jun Myun who was nearby is trying to understand the situation.)

554
00:26:04,153 --> 00:26:05,153
Hold on.

555
00:26:05,154 --> 00:26:06,722
- He should go to the hospital. - Yes.

556
00:26:06,723 --> 00:26:08,123
(The production crew is on it too.)

557
00:26:08,823 --> 00:26:10,162
I think he's seriously hurt. Wait.

558
00:26:10,163 --> 00:26:11,863
(A veteran actor getting too absorbed)

559
00:26:12,563 --> 00:26:13,662
On this side...

560
00:26:13,663 --> 00:26:15,362
(And the sacrificial lamb)

561
00:26:15,363 --> 00:26:16,533
We're in trouble.

562
00:26:17,763 --> 00:26:19,162
(On the verge of tears)

563
00:26:19,163 --> 00:26:20,273
We're really in trouble.

564
00:26:20,903 --> 00:26:22,372
(Are you still clueless?)

565
00:26:22,373 --> 00:26:23,373
(Screaming)

566
00:26:23,973 --> 00:26:25,773
(Kicking hard)

567
00:26:26,173 --> 00:26:28,473
(She's also startled.)

568
00:26:28,873 --> 00:26:30,382
(Writhing in uncontrollable pain)

569
00:26:30,383 --> 00:26:31,483
Are you okay?

570
00:26:35,213 --> 00:26:36,323
I apologize.

571
00:26:38,023 --> 00:26:39,322
Wait. I'm sorry.

572
00:26:39,323 --> 00:26:40,593
(Why can't you recognize me?)

573
00:26:40,793 --> 00:26:42,252
Let me look. It's not swollen,

574
00:26:42,253 --> 00:26:43,653
but you're being a little dramatic.

575
00:26:44,563 --> 00:26:45,693
(Could it be...)

576
00:26:46,193 --> 00:26:47,263
Wait.

577
00:26:49,163 --> 00:26:50,463
(Wait.)

578
00:26:52,033 --> 00:26:53,073
Could it be...

579
00:26:55,933 --> 00:26:57,643
(Peekaboo)

580
00:27:01,113 --> 00:27:02,113
Si Eon!

581
00:27:02,114 --> 00:27:03,443
(Confused, hugging)

582
00:27:03,883 --> 00:27:07,913
(Relieved that he isn't injured and happy to see him)

583
00:27:09,453 --> 00:27:10,652
- Hey. - Si Eon.

584
00:27:10,653 --> 00:27:12,023
You caught on, didn't you?

585
00:27:12,253 --> 00:27:14,323
No, you totally surprised me.

586
00:27:14,623 --> 00:27:15,623
Si Eon.

587
00:27:16,623 --> 00:27:18,022
- It was you? - Yes.

588
00:27:18,023 --> 00:27:19,499
(I can't believe that he's here in the Philippines.)

589
00:27:19,523 --> 00:27:21,393
(Removing the disguise)

590
00:27:25,033 --> 00:27:27,172
(It's so good to see you, Si Eon.)

591
00:27:27,173 --> 00:27:28,403
My lower back. Wait.

592
00:27:29,303 --> 00:27:30,803
I'm going to hurt your lower back.

593
00:27:31,803 --> 00:27:35,013
(Who is it?)

594
00:27:35,143 --> 00:27:36,443
- Who is it? - Si Eon.

595
00:27:37,313 --> 00:27:38,513
- Who is it? - Si Eon.

596
00:27:39,883 --> 00:27:40,953
Hello.

597
00:27:41,213 --> 00:27:42,482
It's Si Eon.

598
00:27:42,483 --> 00:27:43,853
Oh, it's Si Eon.

599
00:27:44,723 --> 00:27:45,723
Goodness.

600
00:27:45,724 --> 00:27:47,352
Jung Ah, we have a guest.

601
00:27:47,353 --> 00:27:48,423
Gosh, hello.

602
00:27:48,653 --> 00:27:50,333
- Hello, Jung Ah. - It's nice to meet you.

603
00:27:50,463 --> 00:27:52,623
- What were you doing here? - I was filming.

604
00:27:54,093 --> 00:27:55,293
(Surprised)

605
00:27:56,163 --> 00:27:57,202
(Sprinting at full speed)

606
00:27:57,203 --> 00:27:58,263
Oh, my.

607
00:28:00,003 --> 00:28:01,303
- Gosh. - Hello, Si Eon.

608
00:28:01,833 --> 00:28:03,042
- Hello. - Did you fly in...

609
00:28:03,043 --> 00:28:04,103
- last night? - Yes.

610
00:28:04,603 --> 00:28:05,763
- Gosh. - It was very tiring.

611
00:28:06,813 --> 00:28:09,442
We invited a guest all the way to the Philippines?

612
00:28:09,443 --> 00:28:11,182
- Seriously. - This is amazing.

613
00:28:11,183 --> 00:28:12,183
I agree.

614
00:28:12,813 --> 00:28:14,683
- It's so good to see you. - Yes.

615
00:28:14,913 --> 00:28:16,882
- It's been very tiring. - I'm so sorry.

616
00:28:16,883 --> 00:28:18,753
Now that I'm done with what I have to do,

617
00:28:19,083 --> 00:28:20,493
- No, Si Eon. - I'll go back.

618
00:28:20,893 --> 00:28:23,022
- It starts now. We have to go. - Pick coconuts. Put on your gloves.

619
00:28:23,023 --> 00:28:24,423
Wait, let me catch my breath.

620
00:28:25,993 --> 00:28:28,763
(Si Eon joins, and the coconut harvest resumes.)

621
00:28:30,263 --> 00:28:31,762
I'll park it here.

622
00:28:31,763 --> 00:28:33,673
While you guys do that, we'll harvest them.

623
00:28:35,703 --> 00:28:37,803
Hye Yoon, you and I will go there to pick them.

624
00:28:37,903 --> 00:28:38,943
Okay.

625
00:28:39,743 --> 00:28:42,413
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven.

626
00:28:43,783 --> 00:28:45,513
Ten. Twenty coconuts.

627
00:28:46,383 --> 00:28:47,683
These are seven coconuts.

628
00:28:48,253 --> 00:28:49,723
- I have 30, and you have 7? - Yes.

629
00:28:50,053 --> 00:28:51,123
We have 37.

630
00:28:52,453 --> 00:28:53,592
We only got one coin so far.

631
00:28:53,593 --> 00:28:55,153
(They obtained 1 coin.)

632
00:28:55,723 --> 00:28:56,723
(What can I do to help, Dex?)

633
00:28:56,724 --> 00:28:58,293
- Do I get on this? - No.

634
00:28:58,623 --> 00:29:00,993
You'll go there and pick coconuts.

635
00:29:01,493 --> 00:29:03,533
Let's walk together.

636
00:29:03,863 --> 00:29:06,162
Let's pick those. I'll transport them.

637
00:29:06,163 --> 00:29:07,243
That sounds good, Jun Myun.

638
00:29:07,873 --> 00:29:09,072
(Meanwhile, Jung Ah is back in action.)

639
00:29:09,073 --> 00:29:11,573
I'll pick all of you at once.

640
00:29:14,443 --> 00:29:17,343
(Grunting)

641
00:29:18,313 --> 00:29:19,313
(Grunting)

642
00:29:19,853 --> 00:29:24,223
(While Jung Ah pushes through by shouting)

643
00:29:24,753 --> 00:29:25,753
Gosh, it's hot.

644
00:29:28,193 --> 00:29:30,293
(Hye Yoon is used to being on the ladder.)

645
00:29:33,333 --> 00:29:34,432
Watch out.

646
00:29:34,433 --> 00:29:37,803
(She harvests 1 as soon as she climbs up.)

647
00:29:38,433 --> 00:29:40,533
(Selecting a stable location)

648
00:29:40,803 --> 00:29:41,902
Ten coconuts and...

649
00:29:41,903 --> 00:29:43,342
(I'll definitely win the high-end meal coupon.)

650
00:29:43,343 --> 00:29:44,403
I'm going to throw it.

651
00:29:48,113 --> 00:29:49,143
Amazing.

652
00:29:51,283 --> 00:29:53,803
(Piling coconuts in the basket that she worked hard to harvest)

653
00:29:54,983 --> 00:29:55,983
Five.

654
00:29:56,953 --> 00:29:57,953
Let's go.

655
00:29:57,954 --> 00:29:59,552
(The basket is filled with coconuts.)

656
00:29:59,553 --> 00:30:00,553
Come this way.

657
00:30:01,423 --> 00:30:02,493
(Dragging)

658
00:30:02,853 --> 00:30:04,293
It's downhill. Stay strong.

659
00:30:04,893 --> 00:30:07,433
(While Hye Yoon's coconuts are being abducted)

660
00:30:08,263 --> 00:30:10,933
(Dex is also working hard to pick coconuts.)

661
00:30:11,333 --> 00:30:13,833
(Clean and decisive chopping)

662
00:30:14,473 --> 00:30:17,103
(Harvesting whole branches at a different scale)

663
00:30:17,803 --> 00:30:20,613
(Handing over to Jun Myun on the transport team)

664
00:30:21,213 --> 00:30:22,842
(Dex harvests them...)

665
00:30:22,843 --> 00:30:24,513
(and passes them to the transport team?)

666
00:30:25,313 --> 00:30:26,582
(A coconut dodging challenge)

667
00:30:26,583 --> 00:30:27,583
Hey!

668
00:30:28,883 --> 00:30:29,883
(Sorry)

669
00:30:29,884 --> 00:30:31,522
Si Eon, what are you doing? You should catch them.

670
00:30:31,523 --> 00:30:33,082
How can I catch them?

671
00:30:33,083 --> 00:30:35,453
Si Eon, there's one more down there.

672
00:30:36,093 --> 00:30:37,733
(He complains but still does everything.)

673
00:30:38,163 --> 00:30:39,463
Si Eon, here you go.

674
00:30:40,633 --> 00:30:41,732
It's extremely heavy.

675
00:30:41,733 --> 00:30:42,992
(Are these grapes or coconuts?)

676
00:30:42,993 --> 00:30:44,033
I got them.

677
00:30:45,533 --> 00:30:48,173
(Transporting coconuts very diligently)

678
00:30:48,703 --> 00:30:51,373
(Gosh, I'm tired.)

679
00:30:52,173 --> 00:30:53,543
Why am I doing this?

680
00:30:56,013 --> 00:30:58,082
(It was better when I was Director Park.)

681
00:30:58,083 --> 00:30:59,283
Jun Myun, I'll carry them.

682
00:31:00,013 --> 00:31:01,412
- They must be heavy. - It's okay.

683
00:31:01,413 --> 00:31:03,773
(Switching on his professional mode in front of his senior)

684
00:31:04,253 --> 00:31:06,053
(Jun Myun is also working hard.)

685
00:31:06,953 --> 00:31:12,522
(Carrying them without a break)

686
00:31:12,523 --> 00:31:13,592
How is it possible to catch them?

687
00:31:13,593 --> 00:31:14,732
(Here's another bunch of coconuts.)

688
00:31:14,733 --> 00:31:15,733
- I got them. - You got them?
- Yes. - Okay.

689
00:31:16,734 --> 00:31:18,232
Just throw them if you can't handle it.

690
00:31:18,233 --> 00:31:19,633
(Here's another bunch of coconuts.)

691
00:31:20,273 --> 00:31:22,133
It's different from Si Eon.

692
00:31:23,203 --> 00:31:24,343
Si Eon, this is great.

693
00:31:26,403 --> 00:31:27,472
It's different.

694
00:31:27,473 --> 00:31:28,942
(Compliments for Si Eon...)

695
00:31:28,943 --> 00:31:31,283
(He flops down without caring about compliments.)

696
00:31:32,113 --> 00:31:35,513
(The sound of hard labor?)

697
00:31:35,713 --> 00:31:37,453
I saw where they fell from above.

698
00:31:39,283 --> 00:31:41,453
(Dex goes to pick up coconuts that rolled away.)

699
00:31:41,593 --> 00:31:42,823
There are so many here.

700
00:31:45,023 --> 00:31:48,263
(Gathering all the runaway coconuts that rolled away)

701
00:31:49,563 --> 00:31:50,602
- Goodness. - Gosh.

702
00:31:50,603 --> 00:31:52,132
(Even the runaway coconuts are collected.)

703
00:31:52,133 --> 00:31:53,273
These are enough now.

704
00:31:54,673 --> 00:31:57,073
- Where did Hye Won go? - She's on her way.

705
00:31:57,773 --> 00:32:00,973
(Hye Yoon is still dragging the coconuts.)

706
00:32:01,943 --> 00:32:04,713
(There's a long way to go, but the coconuts feel impossibly heavy.)

707
00:32:05,283 --> 00:32:09,513
(Struggling)

708
00:32:10,083 --> 00:32:11,552
(This is impossible.)

709
00:32:11,553 --> 00:32:13,693
- Dex! - Yes?

710
00:32:13,993 --> 00:32:15,623
Please help me!

711
00:32:16,393 --> 00:32:17,622
Did you pick a lot?

712
00:32:17,623 --> 00:32:19,163
(Dex)

713
00:32:19,593 --> 00:32:22,662
(Dex rushes over at Hye Yoon's call.)

714
00:32:22,663 --> 00:32:24,303
How many kilograms would these weigh?

715
00:32:24,503 --> 00:32:25,503
What?

716
00:32:25,663 --> 00:32:27,773
It's really difficult. I'll carry two.

717
00:32:28,103 --> 00:32:29,733
- Please help me. - Let it go.

718
00:32:30,243 --> 00:32:31,343
It's really difficult.

719
00:32:32,403 --> 00:32:33,803
Aren't they heavier than you think?

720
00:32:34,273 --> 00:32:35,813
Also, there's a hole.

721
00:32:36,473 --> 00:32:38,383
What? There's a hole?

722
00:32:39,613 --> 00:32:41,382
- Let's go. - Goodness.

723
00:32:41,383 --> 00:32:43,723
(There's a hole at the bottom of the basket.)

724
00:32:43,953 --> 00:32:44,953
Thank you.

725
00:32:45,753 --> 00:32:48,033
I almost couldn't make it over there by the end of today.

726
00:32:50,463 --> 00:32:51,892
(Now that everyone has arrived, it's settlement time.)

727
00:32:51,893 --> 00:32:54,463
Please count them now.

728
00:32:55,593 --> 00:32:57,762
(With 30 coconuts, they already got 1 coin.)

729
00:32:57,763 --> 00:32:59,003
Forty-nine.

730
00:32:59,463 --> 00:33:00,832
There are 50, 51, 52...

731
00:33:00,833 --> 00:33:03,149
(They won the high-end meal coupon with over 50 coconuts.)

732
00:33:03,173 --> 00:33:05,273
Fifty-seven, fifty-eight.

733
00:33:06,503 --> 00:33:07,543
Sixty-seven.

734
00:33:07,643 --> 00:33:09,073
There are 67 up to here.

735
00:33:09,843 --> 00:33:10,843
Seventy.

736
00:33:11,383 --> 00:33:13,653
Seventy-one, seventy-two, seventy-three.

737
00:33:14,683 --> 00:33:17,852
(Will they exceed 80?)

738
00:33:17,853 --> 00:33:18,923
Eighty-four.

739
00:33:19,523 --> 00:33:20,952
- We got more than 80. - We got 86.

740
00:33:20,953 --> 00:33:21,953
We got 86 coconuts.

741
00:33:22,393 --> 00:33:23,562
- Seven. - Eight.

742
00:33:23,563 --> 00:33:24,822
- We have enough. - Nine.

743
00:33:24,823 --> 00:33:25,823
Ten.

744
00:33:25,963 --> 00:33:27,333
With 10 more, we have 90.

745
00:33:28,493 --> 00:33:30,533
- Two, three. - Eight, nine.

746
00:33:31,163 --> 00:33:32,263
- Ten. - Five.

747
00:33:33,373 --> 00:33:34,503
We have 110.

748
00:33:35,703 --> 00:33:38,003
- We have 111, 112... - Including that, we have 111.

749
00:33:39,173 --> 00:33:41,372
We got 112!

750
00:33:41,373 --> 00:33:42,873
(They harvested 112 coconuts.)

751
00:33:43,643 --> 00:33:45,943
(A valuable result of everyone's hard work)

752
00:33:46,883 --> 00:33:49,483
We harvested a lot. Well done, everyone.

753
00:33:49,953 --> 00:33:51,952
I think Hye Yoon harvested about half of them.

754
00:33:51,953 --> 00:33:52,953
Of course.

755
00:33:52,954 --> 00:33:54,823
- Thank you. - Go and get the coins.

756
00:33:54,993 --> 00:33:56,193
Okay, I will.

757
00:33:57,093 --> 00:33:58,122
(The youngest runs over in a flash.)

758
00:33:58,123 --> 00:33:59,192
I will take them.

759
00:33:59,193 --> 00:34:00,662
(The youngest runs over in a flash.)

760
00:34:00,663 --> 00:34:01,663
Okay.

761
00:34:01,963 --> 00:34:03,403
My hands are shaking. I'm so tired.

762
00:34:03,603 --> 00:34:04,833
The high-end meal coupon.

763
00:34:05,663 --> 00:34:08,473
We received the high-end meal coupon.

764
00:34:09,203 --> 00:34:10,243
And...

765
00:34:11,043 --> 00:34:14,973
we also got the ocean view bar coupon.

766
00:34:16,043 --> 00:34:17,542
By inserting a coin,

767
00:34:17,543 --> 00:34:19,782
we hope to get one of those on the very right.

768
00:34:19,783 --> 00:34:21,582
Is there anything that you dislike?

769
00:34:21,583 --> 00:34:23,922
Si Eon, go and take a look.

770
00:34:23,923 --> 00:34:24,923
The ones on the side?

771
00:34:24,924 --> 00:34:26,122
- Yes, among those. - Among these on the side,

772
00:34:26,123 --> 00:34:27,643
is there anything that you don't like?

773
00:34:28,053 --> 00:34:32,323
(Among these, an activity that Si Eon doesn't want to do?)

774
00:34:32,923 --> 00:34:34,203
Something that you'd hate to do.

775
00:34:34,393 --> 00:34:35,833
Who is Hwang Ga Ram?

776
00:34:36,033 --> 00:34:37,133
We don't know either.

777
00:34:37,203 --> 00:34:38,963
Her identity hasn't been revealed yet.

778
00:34:40,273 --> 00:34:41,332
Hwang Ga Ram.

779
00:34:41,333 --> 00:34:43,743
(The siblings don't know who it is either.)

780
00:34:44,803 --> 00:34:46,402
"Late-night walk with Hwang Ga Ram."

781
00:34:46,403 --> 00:34:47,689
(He wouldn't want a late-night walk with Hwang Ga Ram.)

782
00:34:47,713 --> 00:34:48,742
He's shy around strangers.

783
00:34:48,743 --> 00:34:50,482
- It's late at night. - He's shy around strangers,

784
00:34:50,483 --> 00:34:52,312
so he doesn't like to take walks with strangers.

785
00:34:52,313 --> 00:34:54,082
Right? Wouldn't it be uncomfortable?

786
00:34:54,083 --> 00:34:55,752
- Shall we draw one? - Okay.

787
00:34:55,753 --> 00:34:57,283
I'll draw one.

788
00:34:57,823 --> 00:34:58,883
Please.

789
00:34:59,353 --> 00:35:00,552
(Which activity will be drawn?)

790
00:35:00,553 --> 00:35:01,823
What should we get?

791
00:35:02,723 --> 00:35:05,423
- What will it be? - Please let it be something good.

792
00:35:06,193 --> 00:35:07,733
(What?)

793
00:35:09,393 --> 00:35:11,233
- Is it a walk with Hwang Ga Ram? - Wait.

794
00:35:11,963 --> 00:35:13,503
- What? - Yes, I'm sorry.

795
00:35:14,433 --> 00:35:16,872
(Why that one, of all activities?)

796
00:35:16,873 --> 00:35:18,042
That's annoying.

797
00:35:18,043 --> 00:35:19,043
Who's going to do it?

798
00:35:19,443 --> 00:35:20,443
It won't be me, will it?
Is Si Eon Hwang Ga Ram?

799
00:35:21,444 --> 00:35:23,612
- How did I draw... - Aren't you Hwang Ga Ram?

800
00:35:23,613 --> 00:35:26,512
Exactly the one that he didn't want?

801
00:35:26,513 --> 00:35:28,882
None of us hated it other than you.

802
00:35:28,883 --> 00:35:29,983
Who's going to do it?

803
00:35:30,123 --> 00:35:31,723
You have to do it. Who else would it be?

804
00:35:33,253 --> 00:35:35,253
Has Hwang Ga Ram left Korea yet?

805
00:35:36,323 --> 00:35:38,803
If she's taking a walk with us, she should leave Korea by now.

806
00:35:38,863 --> 00:35:41,092
Will Hwang Ga Ram come whenever we want to take...

807
00:35:41,093 --> 00:35:42,132
a walk with her?

808
00:35:42,133 --> 00:35:44,433
We have to contact her in the evening in advance.

809
00:35:44,803 --> 00:35:45,803
She must be nearby.

810
00:35:46,103 --> 00:35:48,333
She must be at her lodging already.

811
00:35:49,773 --> 00:35:51,343
They must also find it ridiculous.

812
00:35:52,903 --> 00:35:54,643
I drew exactly what he disliked.

813
00:35:55,273 --> 00:35:56,273
I know.

814
00:35:56,274 --> 00:35:58,314
(What will be a late-night walk with Hwang Ga Ram?)

815
00:35:58,443 --> 00:36:00,383
We harvested so many.

816
00:36:00,553 --> 00:36:02,312
- Right. - We got very passionate.

817
00:36:02,313 --> 00:36:04,382
We were determined to harvest them today.

818
00:36:04,383 --> 00:36:05,623
- Right. - Goodness.

819
00:36:06,123 --> 00:36:07,792
- Thank you. - Thank you.

820
00:36:07,793 --> 00:36:09,122
- Thank you. - We'll enjoy it.

821
00:36:09,123 --> 00:36:10,322
It's a pineapple.

822
00:36:10,323 --> 00:36:11,362
(Precious)

823
00:36:11,363 --> 00:36:13,323
- It's a golden pineapple. - It's very delicious.

824
00:36:14,633 --> 00:36:16,733
(The coconuts harvested by the siblings)

825
00:36:17,503 --> 00:36:21,173
(They were carried diligently by a water buffalo.)

826
00:36:22,173 --> 00:36:26,743
(They were sent straight to a local market.)

827
00:36:27,413 --> 00:36:31,512
(The siblings head back home after finishing work.)

828
00:36:31,513 --> 00:36:32,943
Didn't you notice it?

829
00:36:33,313 --> 00:36:34,552
- When? Today? - Yes.

830
00:36:34,553 --> 00:36:36,922
Actually, I had no idea today...

831
00:36:36,923 --> 00:36:38,482
because the work was very difficult.

832
00:36:38,483 --> 00:36:39,953
Usually, you're very perceptive.

833
00:36:40,353 --> 00:36:42,452
I resented you more than I noticed you.

834
00:36:42,453 --> 00:36:44,563
- Why? - I turned toward you...

835
00:36:44,993 --> 00:36:47,732
and barely touched your ankle.

836
00:36:47,733 --> 00:36:49,253
- He screamed. - Then you freaked out.

837
00:36:50,033 --> 00:36:52,062
The production crew was worse.

838
00:36:52,063 --> 00:36:54,872
When he screamed, they said, "Call the ambulance."

839
00:36:54,873 --> 00:36:56,002
They were making a huge fuss.

840
00:36:56,003 --> 00:36:57,072
(Everyone was in on the scheme except Dex.)

841
00:36:57,073 --> 00:36:59,042
- They said, "Call 911." - Right.

842
00:36:59,043 --> 00:37:00,203
They were stirring things up.

843
00:37:00,343 --> 00:37:02,973
I touched you really gently like this.

844
00:37:03,583 --> 00:37:05,442
You screamed loudly...

845
00:37:05,443 --> 00:37:07,282
and started kicking me.

846
00:37:07,283 --> 00:37:08,883
(He got startled at the sudden kick.)

847
00:37:09,113 --> 00:37:11,522
- That's when I got dubious. - "Who is this?"

848
00:37:11,523 --> 00:37:14,793
When I looked at him, I recognized the silhouette of his face.

849
00:37:15,553 --> 00:37:16,962
So I lowered his leg.

850
00:37:16,963 --> 00:37:17,963
(It was a success.)

851
00:37:17,964 --> 00:37:18,992
- Mark. - Yes?

852
00:37:18,993 --> 00:37:20,893
This is a new member.

853
00:37:20,933 --> 00:37:21,962
- Yes. - A new member.

854
00:37:21,963 --> 00:37:24,432
He's a very famous actor in Korea.

855
00:37:24,433 --> 00:37:25,602
Hi, Mark.

856
00:37:25,603 --> 00:37:27,133
- Lee Si Eon. - Lee Si Eon?

857
00:37:27,873 --> 00:37:29,672
- Si Eon. - Si Eon?

858
00:37:29,673 --> 00:37:30,743
He's older than me.

859
00:37:31,703 --> 00:37:32,872
It's hard to pronounce it.

860
00:37:32,873 --> 00:37:34,542
"Kim Hye Yoon."

861
00:37:34,543 --> 00:37:36,712
If you're hungry, we have some snacks.

862
00:37:36,713 --> 00:37:37,883
No, I'm fine.

863
00:37:38,043 --> 00:37:39,583
- You don't want any snacks? - No.

864
00:37:40,113 --> 00:37:42,282
- Si Eon. - If I eat snacks...

865
00:37:42,283 --> 00:37:44,352
- In order to get close to her... - Snacks...

866
00:37:44,353 --> 00:37:45,482
Hurry and ask her for some snacks.

867
00:37:45,483 --> 00:37:46,653
I'd like some snacks.

868
00:37:49,223 --> 00:37:50,223
(Is that so?)

869
00:37:50,224 --> 00:37:52,262
It took courage for Jun Myun to say that.

870
00:37:52,263 --> 00:37:53,932
- Isn't that right? - Yes, it took courage.

871
00:37:53,933 --> 00:37:55,333
It definitely took courage for her.

872
00:37:55,433 --> 00:37:57,803
I've never seen Si Eon shy around strangers.

873
00:37:58,163 --> 00:37:59,232
This is new.

874
00:37:59,233 --> 00:38:02,432
Si Eon, you can talk to me without honorifics.

875
00:38:02,433 --> 00:38:04,702
- What? - You can drop the honorifics.

876
00:38:04,703 --> 00:38:06,542
Jung Ah, I also wanted to tell you...

877
00:38:06,543 --> 00:38:08,842
to drop the honorifics with me.

878
00:38:08,843 --> 00:38:11,043
- Then I'll start now. - Okay.

879
00:38:11,913 --> 00:38:13,112
- Please do. - You must be at ease.

880
00:38:13,113 --> 00:38:14,283
I'll be casual from now on.

881
00:38:15,483 --> 00:38:19,682
(As they get to know each other on the way, )

882
00:38:19,683 --> 00:38:23,152
(the sky gets covered with darkness.)

883
00:38:23,153 --> 00:38:25,492
I feel like I've been on the plane and inside a car all day long.

884
00:38:25,493 --> 00:38:29,432
I know. It must feel so frustrating.

885
00:38:29,433 --> 00:38:31,233
We have to make you happy.

886
00:38:31,303 --> 00:38:32,363
It's okay.

887
00:38:32,933 --> 00:38:34,072
I'll treat you well.

888
00:38:34,073 --> 00:38:35,873
I'll show you your room later.

889
00:38:36,703 --> 00:38:38,102
For the next three days, I'll treat you so well...

890
00:38:38,103 --> 00:38:39,503
that you won't be disappointed.

891
00:38:40,203 --> 00:38:43,343
I'll give you many kisses too.

892
00:38:45,843 --> 00:38:49,283
Now that Si Eon is here, your energy has completely changed.

893
00:38:49,553 --> 00:38:51,122
Is it your first time meeting him?

894
00:38:51,123 --> 00:38:52,523
Yes, I met him for the first time.

895
00:38:53,623 --> 00:38:55,492
We never worked together, did we?

896
00:38:55,493 --> 00:38:56,622
- Me? - Yes.

897
00:38:56,623 --> 00:38:57,663
No.

898
00:38:57,893 --> 00:38:59,963
I grew up watching your work.

899
00:39:00,733 --> 00:39:02,092
I've seen a lot of yours too.

900
00:39:02,093 --> 00:39:04,032
I'm a huge fan of "The Big Swindle."

901
00:39:04,033 --> 00:39:05,602
- It's very... - It's a must-see masterpiece.

902
00:39:05,603 --> 00:39:07,232
It's really a masterpiece.

903
00:39:07,233 --> 00:39:09,002
You have to watch...

904
00:39:09,003 --> 00:39:11,203
- Jung Ah's legendary acting. - I agree. It's the best.

905
00:39:11,243 --> 00:39:14,042
Look how gorgeous Jung Ah was.

906
00:39:14,043 --> 00:39:15,113
Take a look at this.

907
00:39:16,313 --> 00:39:18,682
(Jung Ah's stunning beauty back then)

908
00:39:18,683 --> 00:39:20,283
This was Jung Ah's prime.

909
00:39:20,813 --> 00:39:22,152
Stop looking me up.

910
00:39:22,153 --> 00:39:25,452
- Her prime started... - What? I want to look...

911
00:39:25,453 --> 00:39:28,192
- way back then. - at someone beautiful.

912
00:39:28,193 --> 00:39:30,863
Jung Ah, when was your prime?

913
00:39:32,323 --> 00:39:33,592
Every day is her prime.

914
00:39:33,593 --> 00:39:35,863
Dex, that's what you should say.

915
00:39:36,133 --> 00:39:37,133
(Flustered)

916
00:39:37,134 --> 00:39:38,802
If you ask when her prime was,

917
00:39:38,803 --> 00:39:41,433
you're suggesting that her prime is over.

918
00:39:42,373 --> 00:39:43,743
Hye Yoon.

919
00:39:44,203 --> 00:39:46,072
Are you trying to survive alone?

920
00:39:46,073 --> 00:39:47,873
I'm sorry, but I have to survive at least.

921
00:39:49,473 --> 00:39:50,642
I did some socializing.

922
00:39:50,643 --> 00:39:51,682
(Acting coy)

923
00:39:51,683 --> 00:39:52,712
Please understand.

924
00:39:52,713 --> 00:39:54,352
(Learning how to socialize from the youngest)

925
00:39:54,353 --> 00:39:57,852
- Mark, thank you for driving. - Mark, thank you.

926
00:39:57,853 --> 00:40:00,322
- Thank you very much, Mark. - You're welcome.

927
00:40:00,323 --> 00:40:01,883
(Soon, the siblings' car arrives home.)

928
00:40:02,153 --> 00:40:03,192
Let me put this away.

929
00:40:03,193 --> 00:40:05,522
(They return to the lodging with Si Eon.)

930
00:40:05,523 --> 00:40:07,039
- These are some groceries. - I'll take them.

931
00:40:07,063 --> 00:40:08,863
Is it in the back seat?

932
00:40:10,763 --> 00:40:13,332
(Si Eon shares the room with Dex.)

933
00:40:13,333 --> 00:40:14,732
I'll put my stuff here.

934
00:40:14,733 --> 00:40:17,403
(He removes his suitcase for Si Eon.)

935
00:40:17,573 --> 00:40:19,703
- Si Eon, I'm going to work out. - What?

936
00:40:20,973 --> 00:40:24,143
(Dex goes to work out again today.)

937
00:40:25,843 --> 00:40:29,613
(Si eon finally lies down for a minute.)

938
00:40:31,023 --> 00:40:33,283
(Meanwhile, Hye Yoon gets dolled up.)

939
00:40:34,653 --> 00:40:37,123
(Satisfied)

940
00:40:39,893 --> 00:40:41,763
I usually need time like this.

941
00:40:42,093 --> 00:40:44,303
Taking a moment to admire myself in the mirror.

942
00:40:45,133 --> 00:40:46,133
(Laughing)

943
00:40:48,033 --> 00:40:49,202
(Wiggling)

944
00:40:49,203 --> 00:40:51,073
(Her butt seems quite pleased.)

945
00:40:52,603 --> 00:40:55,512
(Please take a look at me.)

946
00:40:55,513 --> 00:40:58,483
When did you get changed into neat overalls?

947
00:40:58,643 --> 00:40:59,812
You have your hand in the pocket.

948
00:40:59,813 --> 00:41:01,412
(Turning around to show off)

949
00:41:01,413 --> 00:41:03,552
I got changed into cute clothes.

950
00:41:03,553 --> 00:41:06,153
- You look pretty. - Thank you.

951
00:41:06,253 --> 00:41:07,293
You look great.

952
00:41:08,753 --> 00:41:11,423
- Did you put rice in the cooker? - Yes.

953
00:41:11,923 --> 00:41:14,793
(Slowly getting ready to cook)

954
00:41:15,793 --> 00:41:17,403
Si Eon, shall we go and cook?

955
00:41:17,863 --> 00:41:18,903
Okay.

956
00:41:21,373 --> 00:41:24,073
(Chef Yum started cooking dinner.)

957
00:41:24,443 --> 00:41:26,442
We're here too.

958
00:41:26,443 --> 00:41:27,512
- Please start. - Okay.

959
00:41:27,513 --> 00:41:28,642
Start on your own.

960
00:41:28,643 --> 00:41:29,743
We have so much to do.

961
00:41:31,443 --> 00:41:33,712
Let me give them to you.

962
00:41:33,713 --> 00:41:34,713
(What to do today)

963
00:41:34,813 --> 00:41:37,753
These are tiger shrimp.

964
00:41:38,353 --> 00:41:40,353
Make barbecue with tiger shrimp?

965
00:41:40,523 --> 00:41:42,552
Grill some shrimp and meat.

966
00:41:42,553 --> 00:41:43,553
With some pineapple.

967
00:41:43,554 --> 00:41:45,823
They're in the basket right in front of you.

968
00:41:45,893 --> 00:41:47,562
- Inside the basket? - Yes.

969
00:41:47,563 --> 00:41:48,963
(Pineapples that were picked today)

970
00:41:49,133 --> 00:41:51,933
(Pineapple is in tonight's dinner menu?)

971
00:41:52,913 --> 00:41:55,813
(Pineapple is in tonight's dinner menu?)

972
00:41:56,353 --> 00:41:59,222
(Morning glory and pork that they bought today)

973
00:41:59,223 --> 00:42:00,452
Let's take it outside.

974
00:42:00,453 --> 00:42:03,193
- Where shall we cook? Let's go. - Okay.

975
00:42:03,723 --> 00:42:05,462
- Let's go outside first. - Yes.

976
00:42:05,463 --> 00:42:06,943
(What dishes will the siblings make?)

977
00:42:07,323 --> 00:42:09,333
(Si Eon comes out to the outdoor kitchen.)

978
00:42:09,893 --> 00:42:12,132
This place seems better than our room.

979
00:42:12,133 --> 00:42:13,439
(He finally takes a look around the siblings' house.)

980
00:42:13,463 --> 00:42:14,902
The swimming pool looks really cool.

981
00:42:14,903 --> 00:42:16,583
(Si Eon also feels like he's on vacation.)

982
00:42:16,873 --> 00:42:18,802
Si Eon, are those shoes big enough?

983
00:42:18,803 --> 00:42:20,502
These shoes are for you.

984
00:42:20,503 --> 00:42:22,672
- Are there shoes for me? - Yes, they have your initials.

985
00:42:22,673 --> 00:42:23,743
Why do they have them?

986
00:42:24,113 --> 00:42:25,142
(A new pair of slippers for Si Eon)

987
00:42:25,143 --> 00:42:26,643
- Thank you. - You're welcome.

988
00:42:26,913 --> 00:42:29,553
(Welcome as the siblings' new family member)

989
00:42:30,283 --> 00:42:31,322
(Si Eon became the third among the siblings.)

990
00:42:31,323 --> 00:42:32,683
I'll wash the shrimp.

991
00:42:33,183 --> 00:42:35,953
- Okay, I'll grill the meat. - Okay.

992
00:42:37,293 --> 00:42:39,123
(Perfect teamwork with Dex)

993
00:42:39,463 --> 00:42:41,232
Here's what I'll make today.

994
00:42:41,233 --> 00:42:42,792
I got inspired in the Philippines.

995
00:42:42,793 --> 00:42:45,863
Grilled skewers are famous here.

996
00:42:46,333 --> 00:42:47,572
What do you like best?

997
00:42:47,573 --> 00:42:51,803
(On the first day of vacation, after declaring it as Dex's favorite dish)

998
00:42:52,443 --> 00:42:53,742
(He also ate some yesterday.)

999
00:42:53,743 --> 00:42:55,342
(He ate...)

1000
00:42:55,343 --> 00:42:57,613
(nonstop.)

1001
00:42:57,913 --> 00:42:59,142
I'll make...

1002
00:42:59,143 --> 00:43:01,352
- grilled pork belly skewers. - As grilled skewers?

1003
00:43:01,353 --> 00:43:02,353
(He wants to make Si Eon taste grilled skewers.)

1004
00:43:02,354 --> 00:43:05,853
Goodness. Since we have a guest,

1005
00:43:06,383 --> 00:43:07,552
even if it's troublesome...

1006
00:43:07,553 --> 00:43:08,693
(The guest)

1007
00:43:10,193 --> 00:43:12,792
Skewers in the Philippines...

1008
00:43:12,793 --> 00:43:14,969
(He plans to make skewers for Si Eon despite the trouble.)

1009
00:43:14,993 --> 00:43:17,633
(On the other hand, Si Eon is in charge of prepping tiger shrimp.)

1010
00:43:18,033 --> 00:43:20,433
(Washing the tiger shrimp 1 by 1)

1011
00:43:21,133 --> 00:43:23,603
- The shrimp are ready. - The shrimp look great.

1012
00:43:24,143 --> 00:43:26,542
(Fresh tiger shrimp, directly from the Philippines, are ready.)

1013
00:43:26,543 --> 00:43:27,943
Shall I grill the shrimp here?

1014
00:43:28,343 --> 00:43:30,143
- Yes, grill them there. - Here?

1015
00:43:30,473 --> 00:43:32,283
Put the charcoal there.

1016
00:43:32,813 --> 00:43:34,713
- Lighting the fire is quite easy. - Yes.

1017
00:43:35,653 --> 00:43:38,482
(Dropping charcoal)

1018
00:43:38,483 --> 00:43:39,923
Oh, it's coconut.

1019
00:43:40,523 --> 00:43:42,252
Is it coconut charcoal?

1020
00:43:42,253 --> 00:43:44,863
- It's coconut charcoal. - That's incredible.

1021
00:43:46,163 --> 00:43:47,163
This is amazing.

1022
00:43:49,563 --> 00:43:51,803
(It's called "the tree of life.")

1023
00:43:52,563 --> 00:43:55,433
(It means that every part of the coconut is usable.)

1024
00:43:56,273 --> 00:43:59,873
(The shells separated from the flesh aren't discarded.)

1025
00:44:01,573 --> 00:44:03,573
(They're gathered in a drum or a pit.)

1026
00:44:05,043 --> 00:44:08,453
(When burned for over 10 hours)

1027
00:44:09,683 --> 00:44:11,553
(Natural coconut charcoal is complete.)

1028
00:44:12,523 --> 00:44:13,882
(It helps eliminate unwanted odors, )

1029
00:44:13,883 --> 00:44:15,843
(so it's perfect to use when grilling over fire.)

1030
00:44:16,093 --> 00:44:17,722
- Lighting the fire will be quick. - Right?

1031
00:44:17,723 --> 00:44:19,163
Wait, is everything ready?

1032
00:44:19,463 --> 00:44:21,033
Jung Ah, can I start a fire now?

1033
00:44:21,133 --> 00:44:23,162
- Yes. - It will light very fast.

1034
00:44:23,163 --> 00:44:24,163
Yes.

1035
00:44:24,803 --> 00:44:26,302
(With lots of confidence...)

1036
00:44:26,303 --> 00:44:27,303
(Igniting)

1037
00:44:28,473 --> 00:44:29,473
(Flaming)

1038
00:44:29,474 --> 00:44:31,373
It won't take long.

1039
00:44:32,343 --> 00:44:33,403
This is good. All right.

1040
00:44:33,843 --> 00:44:37,143
We need to put a few pieces of meat to keep the fire going.

1041
00:44:37,243 --> 00:44:38,782
Put a piece of fat on the grill.

1042
00:44:38,783 --> 00:44:39,783
(Looking like an expert)

1043
00:44:39,784 --> 00:44:40,813
In the center.

1044
00:44:41,313 --> 00:44:42,413
That's good.

1045
00:44:42,753 --> 00:44:45,023
(He plans to keep the fire going with pork fat.)

1046
00:44:45,483 --> 00:44:47,653
Since you're experienced with camping,

1047
00:44:48,123 --> 00:44:50,022
- you're good at this. - This is good.

1048
00:44:50,023 --> 00:44:52,092
- I like it. This is great. - Good.

1049
00:44:52,093 --> 00:44:54,562
(The barbecue is going smoothly.)

1050
00:44:54,563 --> 00:44:58,003
Your cap...

1051
00:44:59,363 --> 00:45:01,173
(Embracing suddenly)

1052
00:45:04,673 --> 00:45:07,072
(Si Eon is no exemption when it comes to Dex's flirting.)

1053
00:45:07,073 --> 00:45:08,393
Don't pretend to be affectionate.

1054
00:45:09,013 --> 00:45:10,372
(Get out of my way.)

1055
00:45:10,373 --> 00:45:11,382
Just a little bit.

1056
00:45:11,383 --> 00:45:12,813
Gosh, the fire went out.

1057
00:45:14,183 --> 00:45:16,453
(Meanwhile, the flame went out.)

1058
00:45:17,113 --> 00:45:20,853
(Using pork fat as a quick fix)

1059
00:45:21,853 --> 00:45:24,222
(In fact, Si Eon's coconut charcoal...)

1060
