(Jung Ah takes out the ingredients from the fridge in advance.)

1825
01:17:35,425 --> 01:17:36,834
(Let's see.)

1826
01:17:36,835 --> 01:17:38,135
The seaweed.

1827
01:17:38,865 --> 01:17:40,935
(She takes out the seaweed from the cabinet...)

1828
01:17:41,905 --> 01:17:44,305
(and lets it soak in water.)

1829
01:17:44,775 --> 01:17:46,875
(Ham, green onion, kimchi, beef)

1830
01:17:47,075 --> 01:17:49,145
(She chops them into bite-sized pieces.)

1831
01:17:49,675 --> 01:17:51,174
Please take out the garlic.

1832
01:17:51,175 --> 01:17:52,215
Okay.

1833
01:17:52,515 --> 01:17:55,245
(Meanwhile, Hye Yoon was in the bedroom.)

1834
01:17:56,385 --> 01:17:58,284
I will be back.

1835
01:17:58,285 --> 01:17:59,724
Have a good workout.

1836
01:17:59,725 --> 01:18:00,725
Will do.

1837
01:18:01,585 --> 01:18:03,354
(She takes out her sneakers from the shoe cabinet.)

1838
01:18:03,355 --> 01:18:05,755
- See you later. - See you later.

1839
01:18:07,365 --> 01:18:09,765
(Is Dex here?)

1840
01:18:10,165 --> 01:18:12,465
(There's no one else in the yard.)

1841
01:18:13,005 --> 01:18:14,005
(Knocking)
Yes?

1842
01:18:15,435 --> 01:18:16,675
Can I come in?

1843
01:18:18,435 --> 01:18:20,204
- Who is it? - Hye Yoon.

1844
01:18:20,205 --> 01:18:21,744
- I mean... - Dex is in the shower, right now.

1845
01:18:21,745 --> 01:18:23,514
He is? Okay.

1846
01:18:23,515 --> 01:18:24,814
Are you going to the gym?

1847
01:18:24,815 --> 01:18:26,714
Yes. We were supposed to meet at 9am,

1848
01:18:26,715 --> 01:18:28,985
and it's already 9:02am.

1849
01:18:29,985 --> 01:18:31,654
I'll let him know.

1850
01:18:31,655 --> 01:18:33,724
- Yes, please rush him. - Sure.

1851
01:18:33,725 --> 01:18:36,655
Dex, she wants you to hurry.

1852
01:18:37,695 --> 01:18:40,395
Why is he just now taking a shower?

1853
01:18:40,665 --> 01:18:42,395
It's 9:02am right now.

1854
01:18:42,495 --> 01:18:44,635
It will take us some time to get there.

1855
01:18:44,735 --> 01:18:46,765
We have to get back, eat breakfast,

1856
01:18:46,865 --> 01:18:49,005
and go diving in the jungle.

1857
01:18:49,735 --> 01:18:50,775
Right?

1858
01:18:52,135 --> 01:18:54,475
(Time is gold.)

1859
01:18:55,275 --> 01:18:56,645
Goodness.

1860
01:18:57,345 --> 01:18:59,815
(Hye Yoon decides to wait inside the house.)

1861
01:18:59,915 --> 01:19:01,245
Guess what?

1862
01:19:02,085 --> 01:19:04,115
Dex is in the shower.

1863
01:19:04,355 --> 01:19:07,354
You need to wash up before you work out.

1864
01:19:07,355 --> 01:19:09,225
Yes.

1865
01:19:09,695 --> 01:19:10,824
He showers a lot.

1866
01:19:10,825 --> 01:19:13,765
(He showers a lot.)

1867
01:19:13,995 --> 01:19:15,924
Will we be able to leave at 11am?

1868
01:19:15,925 --> 01:19:17,164
What if we get delayed again?

1869
01:19:17,165 --> 01:19:18,294
We can't be late because of you working out.

1870
01:19:18,295 --> 01:19:20,464
Don't spend too much time at the gym.

1871
01:19:20,465 --> 01:19:22,064
- Do a quick workout. - You need to go there and back,

1872
01:19:22,065 --> 01:19:23,135
and it's already 9am.

1873
01:19:23,235 --> 01:19:24,804
Wait, why are we saying all this to Hye Yoon?

1874
01:19:24,805 --> 01:19:27,344
Right. It's not her fault.

1875
01:19:27,345 --> 01:19:28,674
(Hye Yoon was being scolded without doing anything wrong.)

1876
01:19:28,675 --> 01:19:31,375
Why is he taking a shower when you two should be leaving?

1877
01:19:32,645 --> 01:19:33,945
Dex, come on.

1878
01:19:34,485 --> 01:19:35,585
Good morning.

1879
01:19:37,115 --> 01:19:38,285
Good morning.

1880
01:19:38,755 --> 01:19:39,755
(Startled)

1881
01:19:40,125 --> 01:19:41,755
- You're here. - You're here.

1882
01:19:42,585 --> 01:19:43,594
Did you sleep well?

1883
01:19:43,595 --> 01:19:45,154
- Let's get going. - Hurry.

1884
01:19:45,155 --> 01:19:47,124
- We're heading to the gym. - Hey, Dex!

1885
01:19:47,125 --> 01:19:48,125
- Yes? - What time will you be back?

1886
01:19:48,126 --> 01:19:50,265
You have to hurry back. We have to leave at 11am.

1887
01:19:50,995 --> 01:19:52,095
We'll be back on time.

1888
01:19:52,195 --> 01:19:53,335
What are we riding?

1889
01:19:54,805 --> 01:19:57,635
(They decide to take the motorcycle.)

1890
01:19:58,035 --> 01:20:00,205
I have no personal experience riding motorcycles.

1891
01:20:01,005 --> 01:20:02,045
Personal experience?

1892
01:20:02,245 --> 01:20:03,844
I've only been on them when I was filming.

1893
01:20:03,845 --> 01:20:05,321
(This is Hye Yoon's first time riding a motorcycle.)

1894
01:20:05,345 --> 01:20:07,785
(And her brother, Dex, is there for her first time.)

1895
01:20:08,815 --> 01:20:11,215
(Hop on.)

1896
01:20:11,285 --> 01:20:12,885
- I'm getting on the motorcycle. - Okay.

1897
01:20:14,085 --> 01:20:15,124
(Getting on the motorcycle)

1898
01:20:15,125 --> 01:20:17,024
Put your legs here.

1899
01:20:17,025 --> 01:20:18,095
- Here? - Yes.

1900
01:20:19,425 --> 01:20:21,064
- I'm scared. - Hold on to whatever you can.

1901
01:20:21,065 --> 01:20:22,194
Hold on tightly.

1902
01:20:22,195 --> 01:20:23,695
(Tightly)

1903
01:20:24,265 --> 01:20:26,965
Excuse me. I can't die, Dex.

1904
01:20:27,505 --> 01:20:29,735
- I have to survive somehow. - All right.

1905
01:20:30,605 --> 01:20:32,634
That's a sure way to buckle your seatbelt.

1906
01:20:32,635 --> 01:20:34,104
Dex, that looks fun.

1907
01:20:34,105 --> 01:20:35,144
We'll be back.

1908
01:20:35,145 --> 01:20:36,574
- Do you want to join us? - No.

1909
01:20:36,575 --> 01:20:37,774
(They say goodbye to Si Eon, who came to see them off.)

1910
01:20:37,775 --> 01:20:39,274
- Let's go. - Drive safe.

1911
01:20:39,275 --> 01:20:40,514
- Let's get going. - Let's get going.

1912
01:20:40,515 --> 01:20:41,515
We're leaving!

1913
01:20:41,516 --> 01:20:43,715
- Goodness. - Bye.

1914
01:20:44,955 --> 01:20:47,525
(They start riding down the alley in front of the house.)

1915
01:20:48,485 --> 01:20:50,755
(Goodness)

1916
01:20:51,025 --> 01:20:53,864
If I fall while riding this with an actress on the back,

1917
01:20:53,865 --> 01:20:54,865
that would be a major accident.

1918
01:20:54,866 --> 01:20:56,795
(Joking)

1919
01:20:58,165 --> 01:21:00,634
I trust you to drive safely.

1920
01:21:00,635 --> 01:21:01,665
Hello.

1921
01:21:02,405 --> 01:21:03,804
- Hey, Mark! - It's Mark!

1922
01:21:03,805 --> 01:21:06,005
(They exchange greetings with Mark, who was nearby.)

1923
01:21:06,475 --> 01:21:08,875
(They speed down the road with the wind on their face.)

1924
01:21:10,275 --> 01:21:12,315
- The weather is so nice. - It is.

1925
01:21:13,745 --> 01:21:16,114
(The bright weather...)

1926
01:21:16,115 --> 01:21:17,854
(and the closeness of the scenery in the Philippines...)

1927
01:21:17,855 --> 01:21:19,984
- It feels like we're on a drive. - Yes.

1928
01:21:19,985 --> 01:21:22,561
(makes it feel like they're out on a drive, not heading to the gym.)

1929
01:21:22,585 --> 01:21:24,124
This is so great.

1930
01:21:24,125 --> 01:21:25,595
It is? I'm glad.

1931
01:21:26,565 --> 01:21:28,864
The weather is doing us a favor for this trip.

1932
01:21:28,865 --> 01:21:29,865
It is.

1933
01:21:31,165 --> 01:21:32,664
(Meanwhile, at the house)

1934
01:21:32,665 --> 01:21:35,165
- Jung Ah. - Si Eon, you're up.

1935
01:21:35,635 --> 01:21:36,835
Is there anything I can do?

1936
01:21:38,135 --> 01:21:40,021
We're going to set the table. Wipe the table too.

1937
01:21:40,045 --> 01:21:41,045
Go on a walk?

1938
01:21:42,375 --> 01:21:43,714
(Laughing)

1939
01:21:43,715 --> 01:21:44,814
Sure, go on a walk.

1940
01:21:44,815 --> 01:21:47,014
No, she meant set the table. We're going to be eating here.

1941
01:21:47,015 --> 01:21:48,284
- It takes no time. - Right here.

1942
01:21:48,285 --> 01:21:49,784
I see. Set the table.

1943
01:21:49,785 --> 01:21:51,154
(Si Eon is still half asleep.)

1944
01:21:51,155 --> 01:21:52,684
Have a seat and drink some coffee.

1945
01:21:52,685 --> 01:21:53,685
Right, drink some coffee.

1946
01:21:53,686 --> 01:21:55,585
Listen to some music and drink some coffee.

1947
01:21:56,225 --> 01:21:59,055
(They give Si Eon a cup of coffee.)

1948
01:21:59,595 --> 01:22:02,825
(I will give you all)

1949
01:22:02,895 --> 01:22:05,734
You're singing a Buzz song this morning?

1950
01:22:05,735 --> 01:22:07,734
This is Lee Seung Chul's song.

1951
01:22:07,735 --> 01:22:08,865
- I see. - Yes.

1952
01:22:09,335 --> 01:22:10,374
Okay.

1953
01:22:10,375 --> 01:22:12,011
("I Will Give You All" by Lee Seung Chul)

1954
01:22:12,035 --> 01:22:15,475
(You don't need water in soaked seaweed.)

1955
01:22:16,345 --> 01:22:19,575
(After squeezing the water out, cut the seaweed into small pieces.)

1956
01:22:20,485 --> 01:22:23,855
(Move the seaweed into a bowl.)

1957
01:22:24,115 --> 01:22:26,825
(It is ready to be stir-fried with the beef she chopped earlier.)

1958
01:22:26,925 --> 01:22:30,495
(First, she puts the beef and cooking wine into the pot.)

1959
01:22:30,655 --> 01:22:36,535
(She stir-fries the beef with cooking wine to remove any smell.)

1960
01:22:37,235 --> 01:22:41,035
(I will give you all)

1961
01:22:41,305 --> 01:22:44,575
(The beef is cooked just right as Jung Ah keeps giving her all.)

1962
01:22:44,935 --> 01:22:48,304
(She adds some sesame oil for a nutty flavor.)

1963
01:22:48,305 --> 01:22:49,305
All right.

1964
01:22:49,306 --> 01:22:52,775
(The seaweed is the star of seaweed soup.)

1965
01:22:53,345 --> 01:22:56,485
(She doesn't waste a single piece of seaweed.)

1966
01:22:57,015 --> 01:23:00,255
(The beef and seaweed are stir-fried together with sesame oil.)

1967
01:23:00,825 --> 01:23:01,855
(Soup soy sauce)

1968
01:23:02,085 --> 01:23:04,525
(She adds soup soy sauce to season the soup.)

1969
01:23:04,925 --> 01:23:07,895
(Don't forget the minced garlic.)

1970
01:23:09,165 --> 01:23:10,165
(A big spoonful)

1971
01:23:11,165 --> 01:23:12,285
(Plus another half spoonful)

1972
01:23:12,495 --> 01:23:16,535
(Lastly, she pours water into the pot.)

1973
01:23:16,735 --> 01:23:19,704
And then we let it simmer until it's nicely reduced.

1974
01:23:19,705 --> 01:23:22,175
(Once it simmers, the seaweed soup is complete!)

1975
01:23:22,575 --> 01:23:23,714
(While the younger siblings enjoy their morning...)

1976
01:23:23,715 --> 01:23:24,845
(eating apples, )

1977
01:23:26,245 --> 01:23:28,514
(Jung Ah begins making kimchi fried rice.)

1978
01:23:28,515 --> 01:23:29,515
All right.

1979
01:23:29,516 --> 01:23:31,185
(Pouring in cooking oil)

1980
01:23:31,915 --> 01:23:33,915
(Throwing in the chopped green onion onto the pan)

1981
01:23:33,955 --> 01:23:36,155
(She infuses the oil with the green onion.)

1982
01:23:37,225 --> 01:23:39,995
(Then she adds ham that she cut into tiny pieces earlier.)

1983
01:23:40,665 --> 01:23:43,935
(She stir-fries everything together to infuse the aroma of green onion.)

1984
01:23:44,195 --> 01:23:46,965
(Now, it's time for the kimchi!)

1985
01:23:47,405 --> 01:23:48,405
(Pause!)

1986
01:23:49,065 --> 01:23:50,335
Is this too much kimchi?

1987
01:23:51,535 --> 01:23:52,605
Whatever!

1988
01:23:53,645 --> 01:23:56,445
(You think there's too much kimchi?)

1989
01:23:57,445 --> 01:24:01,615
("Then put in a lot of rice," says the Generous Chef.)

1990
01:24:02,015 --> 01:24:04,375
(The kimchi fried rice is tossed around like it's dancing.)

1991
01:24:07,625 --> 01:24:09,955
(Sesame oil for a deeper flavor.)

1992
01:24:11,355 --> 01:24:13,225
- Sesame seeds. Si Eon! - Sesame seeds?

1993
01:24:13,765 --> 01:24:15,794
- It might be out there. - It says "roasted sesame seeds."

1994
01:24:15,795 --> 01:24:17,695
Yes, that's it. Sprinkle them in.

1995
01:24:18,295 --> 01:24:20,034
As much as you want.

1996
01:24:20,035 --> 01:24:21,534
(As much sesame seeds as Si Eon wants)

1997
01:24:21,535 --> 01:24:23,234
We have to fry eggs.

1998
01:24:23,235 --> 01:24:24,955
- To go on top of the fried rice. - Got it.

1999
01:24:25,235 --> 01:24:28,045
We'll do that once you're done with the food.

2000
01:24:28,145 --> 01:24:32,015
(Lastly, sprinkle black pepper.)

2001
01:24:32,775 --> 01:24:37,115
(The Generous Chef takes a bite.)

2002
01:24:37,615 --> 01:24:39,614
(It's good.)

2003
01:24:39,615 --> 01:24:41,085
- Is the food ready? - Taste it.

2004
01:24:42,755 --> 01:24:44,525
(Taking a bite)

2005
01:24:45,195 --> 01:24:46,255
It's good, isn't it?

2006
01:24:47,095 --> 01:24:48,295
Si Eon, try this.

2007
01:24:48,865 --> 01:24:51,095
(Si Eon gets to taste it too.)

2008
01:24:54,405 --> 01:24:55,535
- It's good. - It's good.

2009
01:24:55,935 --> 01:24:57,175
Jung Ah, this is so good.

2010
01:24:57,635 --> 01:24:59,275
Jung Ah, it's good. It has a clean taste.

2011
01:24:59,305 --> 01:25:01,505
- It tastes very clean. - Right.

2012
01:25:02,475 --> 01:25:04,215
Jung Ah is such a good cook.

2013
01:25:05,175 --> 01:25:07,145
Need I say more.

2014
01:25:07,915 --> 01:25:10,215
So she's good at acting,

2015
01:25:10,585 --> 01:25:11,984
good at cooking,

2016
01:25:11,985 --> 01:25:13,485
and is beautiful.

2017
01:25:13,885 --> 01:25:16,355
That's why my husband loves me, don't you think so?

2018
01:25:19,055 --> 01:25:21,065
- A private matter between couples. - Right.

2019
01:25:22,395 --> 01:25:24,634
- I can't really say... - Jung Ah is in such a good mood...

2020
01:25:24,635 --> 01:25:26,035
that it's like she's on cloud nine.

2021
01:25:26,395 --> 01:25:28,865
(Smiling)

2022
01:25:29,705 --> 01:25:32,405
(Meanwhile, the youngest siblings are at the gym.)

2023
01:25:34,145 --> 01:25:36,774
(Hye Yoon found a pair of gloves.)

2024
01:25:36,775 --> 01:25:38,745
Don't mind me.

2025
01:25:39,215 --> 01:25:40,585
I'll just put these here.

2026
01:25:41,885 --> 01:25:43,355
Do you box?

2027
01:25:43,515 --> 01:25:47,054
I don't want to get in the way of your upper body day.

2028
01:25:47,055 --> 01:25:48,084
You do you.

2029
01:25:48,085 --> 01:25:49,755
Wait, you said you learned how to box.

2030
01:25:50,225 --> 01:25:52,355
I did learn,

2031
01:25:52,695 --> 01:25:54,065
but I'm bad at it.

2032
01:25:54,625 --> 01:25:55,865
I'm not good at it, either.

2033
01:25:57,535 --> 01:25:59,564
I'm really bad at it. What do you think?

2034
01:25:59,565 --> 01:26:00,734
(Hye Yoon tries some light footwork.)

2035
01:26:00,735 --> 01:26:01,835
That's good.

2036
01:26:03,675 --> 01:26:05,805
(Interested)

2037
01:26:06,975 --> 01:26:09,105
(While she's at it, she throws a one-two.)

2038
01:26:09,975 --> 01:26:11,075
Nice.

2039
01:26:11,815 --> 01:26:12,945
This is so embarrassing.

2040
01:26:13,515 --> 01:26:16,915
The person next to us looks like a boxing master.

2041
01:26:17,915 --> 01:26:19,014
I'm scared.

2042
01:26:19,015 --> 01:26:20,624
(The mysterious man has an extraordinary aura.)

2043
01:26:20,625 --> 01:26:22,555
Sports are all about confidence.

2044
01:26:24,325 --> 01:26:25,525
Okay.

2045
01:26:26,995 --> 01:26:29,025
Nice posture.

2046
01:26:29,565 --> 01:26:32,135
I'll hold onto it.

2047
01:26:32,865 --> 01:26:33,904
Go one-two.

2048
01:26:33,905 --> 01:26:36,434
(The two siblings begin their boxing training.)

2049
01:26:36,435 --> 01:26:37,674
Sports are all about confidence.

2050
01:26:37,675 --> 01:26:40,575
(Sports are all about confidence.)

2051
01:26:40,805 --> 01:26:41,805
(Staring)

2052
01:26:41,806 --> 01:26:43,175
(As the master shows interest, )

2053
01:26:43,815 --> 01:26:46,145
(Hye Yoon loses confidence.)

2054
01:26:46,375 --> 01:26:47,985
(Thinking)

2055
01:26:48,445 --> 01:26:49,914
How do you hit a punching bag properly?

2056
01:26:49,915 --> 01:26:51,084
(Dex approaches the mysterious man.)

2057
01:26:51,085 --> 01:26:52,984
Sir, do you provide boxing training?

2058
01:26:52,985 --> 01:26:54,025
Yes.

2059
01:26:54,855 --> 01:26:56,794
Can you help us?

2060
01:26:56,795 --> 01:26:58,124
(Once again, Dex asks to learn.)

2061
01:26:58,125 --> 01:27:00,594
You're our senior. We're not good.

2062
01:27:00,595 --> 01:27:02,715
- We'll start with the one-two. - Not good at boxing.

2063
01:27:02,895 --> 01:27:04,564
The one-two? Yes. Can you, please?

2064
01:27:04,565 --> 01:27:05,565
Yes.

2065
01:27:06,395 --> 01:27:07,835
He really is a master.

2066
01:27:08,405 --> 01:27:09,934
Who's going to start first?

2067
01:27:09,935 --> 01:27:10,975
It's me.

2068
01:27:11,635 --> 01:27:12,705
Bend your knees.

2069
01:27:13,645 --> 01:27:15,645
Cover your chin. Cover your jaw.

2070
01:27:15,975 --> 01:27:18,295
If I say "one," you're going to punch with your left hand.

2071
01:27:19,375 --> 01:27:20,385
One.

2072
01:27:20,815 --> 01:27:21,815
Beautiful.

2073
01:27:22,515 --> 01:27:23,715
Speed! One-two!

2074
01:27:24,655 --> 01:27:25,684
Speed!

2075
01:27:25,685 --> 01:27:26,884
(Dex is progressing a bit faster.)

2076
01:27:26,885 --> 01:27:28,024
Okay. One-two!

2077
01:27:28,025 --> 01:27:30,105
(Hye Yoon is learning step by step from the basics.)

2078
01:27:30,195 --> 01:27:32,854
(The siblings' gym in Bohol)

2079
01:27:32,855 --> 01:27:34,565
(Dex is the ace.)

2080
01:27:34,795 --> 01:27:35,865
You're good.

2081
01:27:36,465 --> 01:27:37,465
Go. One-two!

2082
01:27:37,466 --> 01:27:39,764
(Full of enthusiasm)

2083
01:27:39,765 --> 01:27:41,604
Go. One-two, one-two!

2084
01:27:41,605 --> 01:27:42,665
That's it.

